Correlation of clinical data of TCGA-LUAD and hsa-miR-944 expression

Loading data

library("miRBaseConverter")

clinical <- readRDS('E:\\Drmowla\\LungCancer\\LUAD\\TCGA_LUAD_Clinical2.rds')
data_orig <- readRDS('E:\\Drmowla\\LungCancer\\LUAD\\TCGA_LUAD_miRNA2.rds')

DataTumor <- data_orig[,grepl("01A",colnames(data_orig))|grepl("01B",colnames(data_orig))]
colnames(DataTumor) <- substr(colnames(DataTumor),1,12)
rownames(DataTumor) <- miRNA_AccessionToName(rownames(DataTumor),targetVersion = "v21")$TargetName


clinicalTumor <- clinical[grepl("01A",colnames(data_orig))|grepl("01B",colnames(data_orig)),]
#clinicalTumor$bcr_patient_barcode <- gsub("-", ".", clinicalTumor$bcr_patient_barcode)
uniqueidx <- sapply(unique(clinicalTumor$bcr_patient_barcode),function(x)which(clinicalTumor$bcr_patient_barcode==x)[1])
clinicalTumor <- clinicalTumor[uniqueidx,]
rownames(clinicalTumor) <- clinicalTumor$bcr_patient_barcode

Correlation of Categorial data

gender

#DT::datatable(as.data.frame(table(clinical$gender)))

CurrExpr <- copy944[intersectedsamples]
CurrExpr <- CurrExpr[clinicalTumor[intersectedsamples,]$gender!="" ]

CurrLabels <- clinicalTumor[intersectedsamples,]$gender[clinicalTumor[intersectedsamples,]$gender!=""]

StatSum <- lapply(names(table(CurrLabels)), function(x)c(mean(as.numeric(CurrExpr[CurrLabels==x])),sd(as.numeric(CurrExpr[CurrLabels==x]))/sqrt(sum(CurrLabels==x))))
StatSumDF <- do.call(rbind, StatSum)

#StatSum <- lapply(names(table(CurrLabels)), function(x)summary(as.numeric(CurrExpr[CurrLabels==x])))
#StatSumDF <- do.call(rbind, StatSum)

SumToShow <- cbind(table(CurrLabels),StatSumDF)
colnames(SumToShow) <- c("#N", "Avg", "CV")
DT::datatable(as.data.frame(SumToShow))
#table(clinical$stage_event_pathologic_stage)
dataorigagg <-  data.frame(CurrExpr=as.numeric(CurrExpr),clinical=CurrLabels)

#dataorigagg <-  data.frame(CopyNumber=as.numeric(copy944[intersectedsamples]),clinical=clinicalTumor[intersectedsamples,]$race_list)
res.aov <- t.test(CurrExpr ~ clinical, data = dataorigagg)
(res.aov)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  CurrExpr by clinical
## t = -0.12026, df = 412.54, p-value = 0.9043
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means between group FEMALE and group MALE is not equal to 0

## mean in group FEMALE   mean in group MALE

Survival analysis

CurrmiR <- as.numeric(copy944[intersectedsamples])
survival.data_func <- data.frame(time=as.numeric(clinicalTumor[intersectedsamples,]$days_to_last_followup),patient=clinicalTumor[intersectedsamples,]$bcr_patient_barcode,vital_status=as.character(clinicalTumor[intersectedsamples,]$vital_status),CopyNum=as.numeric(CurrmiR))

survival.data_func$time[which(survival.data_func$vital_status=="Dead")] <- as.numeric(clinicalTumor[intersectedsamples,]$days_to_death[which(survival.data_func$vital_status=="Dead")])

survival.data_func$vital_status[which(survival.data_func$vital_status=="Alive")] <- "0"
survival.data_func$vital_status[which(survival.data_func$vital_status=="Dead")] <- "1"
survival.data_func$vital_status <- as.numeric(survival.data_func$vital_status)
survival.data_func$time <- as.numeric(survival.data_func$time)
#survival.data_func <- survival.data_func[survival.data_func$time>0,]
library(TCGAbiolinks)
library(survminer)
library(survival)
## 
## Attaching package: 'survival'
## The following object is masked from 'package:survminer':
## 
##     myeloma
BRCA.surv_rnaseq.cut_func <- surv_cutpoint(
   survival.data_func,
   time = "time",
   event = "vital_status",
   variables = c("CopyNum")
)
#print(summary(BRCA.surv_rnaseq.cut_func))
#print(plot(BRCA.surv_rnaseq.cut_func, "miR", palette = "npg"))

BRCAsurv_rnaseqcat_func <- surv_categorize(BRCA.surv_rnaseq.cut_func) 
#formulaobj <- as.formula(paste(c("Surv(time, vital_status) ~ ",CurrmiRnametmp),collapse = ""))
#print(formulaobj)

fit_func <- survfit(Surv(time, vital_status) ~ CopyNum,data = BRCAsurv_rnaseqcat_func)

cox_model <- coxph(Surv(time, vital_status) ~ CopyNum,data = BRCAsurv_rnaseqcat_func)
# Extract the hazard ratio for group 2 compared to group 1
hazard_ratio <- format(1.0/as.numeric(summary(cox_model)$conf.int[1]), digits=4, nsmall=3) 

# Print the hazard ratio and its confidence interval
print(hazard_ratio)
## [1] "1.348"
ggsurv <- ggsurvplot(
   fit_func,                     # survfit object with calculated statistics.
   data = BRCAsurv_rnaseqcat_func,
   risk.table = TRUE,       # show risk table.
   pval = TRUE,             # show p-value of log-rank test.
   conf.int = TRUE,         # show confidence intervals for 
                            # point estimaes of survival curves.
    xlim = c(0,4000),        # present narrower X axis, but not affect
                            # survival estimates.
   break.time.by = 365,    # break X axis in time intervals by 250.
 risk.table.y.text.col = T, # colour risk table text annotations.
  risk.table.y.text = FALSE # show bars instead of names in text annotations
                            # in legend of risk table
)

# customised the plot
ggsurv$plot <- ggsurv$plot +
  ggplot2::annotate(
    "text",
    x = 325, y = 0.25,
    label = paste0("HR = ",hazard_ratio,collapse = ""),
    size = 5
  )

print(ggsurv)

clinical.fu.new <- as.data.frame(clinical.fu.v1$clinical_follow_up_v1.0_luad)
colnames(clinical.fu.new) <- clinical.fu.new[1,]
clinical.fu.new <- clinical.fu.new[c(-1,-2),]
clinical.fu.new$days_to_death <- as.numeric(clinical.fu.new$days_to_death)
clinical.fu.new$days_to_last_followup <- as.numeric(clinical.fu.new$days_to_last_followup)

tmpcnt1 <- 0
tmpcnt2 <- 0
tmpcnt3 <- 0

for(count in seq(1,nrow(clinical.fu.new),1)){
  CurrOrgIdx <- which(clinical.fu.new$bcr_patient_barcode[count]==clinical.patient.df$bcr_patient_barcode)
  if(clinical.patient.df$vital_status[CurrOrgIdx]=="Alive" & clinical.fu.new$vital_status[count]=="Alive"){
    if(is.na(clinical.patient.df[CurrOrgIdx,]$days_to_last_followup)){
      clinical.patient.df[CurrOrgIdx,]$days_to_last_followup <- clinical.fu.new[count,]$days_to_last_followup
      tmpcnt1 <- tmpcnt1 + 1
    }else{
      if(!is.na(clinical.fu.new[count,]$days_to_last_followup)& clinical.fu.new[count,]$days_to_last_followup>clinical.patient.df[CurrOrgIdx,]$days_to_last_followup)
        clinical.patient.df[CurrOrgIdx,]$days_to_last_followup <- clinical.fu.new[count,]$days_to_last_followup
        tmpcnt2 <- tmpcnt2 + 1
    }
  }
  if(clinical.patient.df$vital_status[CurrOrgIdx]=="Alive" & clinical.fu.new$vital_status[count]=="Dead"){
      clinical.patient.df[CurrOrgIdx,]$days_to_last_followup <- clinical.fu.new[count,]$days_to_last_followup
      clinical.patient.df[CurrOrgIdx,]$days_to_death <- clinical.fu.new[count,]$days_to_death
      clinical.patient.df[CurrOrgIdx,]$vital_status <- clinical.fu.new[count,]$vital_status
      tmpcnt3 <- tmpcnt3 + 1
  }
}
